{"parse":{"title":"Bust of Monsignor Pedro de Foix Montoya","pageid":32981548,"revid":841919253,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vevent\" style=\"width:22em;width: 22em; line-height: 1.4em; text-align: left; float:;\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"summary\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-size: 125%; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic\">Bust of Monsignor Pedro de Foix Montoya</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Bernini,_ritratto_di_Pedro_de_Foix_Montoya.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Bernini, ritratto di Pedro de Foix Montoya.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2f/Bernini%2C_ritratto_di_Pedro_de_Foix_Montoya.jpg/220px-Bernini%2C_ritratto_di_Pedro_de_Foix_Montoya.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"262\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2f/Bernini%2C_ritratto_di_Pedro_de_Foix_Montoya.jpg/330px-Bernini%2C_ritratto_di_Pedro_de_Foix_Montoya.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2f/Bernini%2C_ritratto_di_Pedro_de_Foix_Montoya.jpg/440px-Bernini%2C_ritratto_di_Pedro_de_Foix_Montoya.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"840\" data-file-height=\"1000\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Artist</th><td class=\"attendee\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Gian_Lorenzo_Bernini\" title=\"Gian Lorenzo Bernini\">Gian Lorenzo Bernini</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Year</th><td>\n1621\u201322<span style=\"display:none\">&#160;(<span class=\"bday dtstart published updated\">1621\u201322</span>)</span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Catalogue</th><td>\n13</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Type</th><td class=\"category\">\nSculpture</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Medium</th><td class=\"category\">\nMarble</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Dimensions</th><td>\nLife-size</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Location</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Santa_Maria_di_Monserrato\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Santa Maria di Monserrato\">Santa Maria di Monserrato</a>, Rome</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\"><span style=\"display:none\"><a href=\"/wiki/Geographic_coordinate_system\" title=\"Geographic coordinate system\">Coordinates</a></span></th><td>\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span id=\"coordinates\"><a href=\"/wiki/Geographic_coordinate_system\" title=\"Geographic coordinate system\">Coordinates</a>: <span class=\"plainlinks nourlexpansion\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//tools.wmflabs.org/geohack/geohack.php?pagename=Bust_of_Monsignor_Pedro_de_Foix_Montoya&amp;params=41_53_45.40_N_12_28_08.69_E_type:landmark\"><span class=\"geo-default\"><span class=\"geo-dms\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\"><span class=\"latitude\">41\u00b053\u203245.40\u2033N</span> <span class=\"longitude\">12\u00b028\u203208.69\u2033E</span></span></span><span class=\"geo-multi-punct\">&#xfeff; / &#xfeff;</span><span class=\"geo-nondefault\"><span class=\"geo-dec\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\">41.8959444\u00b0N 12.4690806\u00b0E</span><span style=\"display:none\">&#xfeff; / <span class=\"geo\">41.8959444; 12.4690806</span></span></span></a></span></span></span></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>Bust of Monsignor Pedro de Foix Montoya</b></i> is a sculpted portrait by the Italian artist <a href=\"/wiki/Gianlorenzo_Bernini\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gianlorenzo Bernini\">Gianlorenzo Bernini</a>. Executed in 1621 and 1622, it sits within a larger tomb created for Montoya, a Spanish lawyer working in Rome. The tomb was originally in the Spanish national church in Rome, <a href=\"/wiki/San_Giacomo_degli_Spagnuoli\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"San Giacomo degli Spagnuoli\">San Giacomo degli Spagnuoli</a>, but was moved in the nineteenth century when the church fell out of Spanish possession. The monument now sits in the refectory attached to the Roman church of <a href=\"/wiki/Santa_Maria_di_Monserrato\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Santa Maria di Monserrato\">Santa Maria di Monserrato</a>. The architecture for the tomb was undertaken by <a href=\"/wiki/Orazio_Turriani\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Orazio Turriani\">Orazio Turriani</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bust_of_Monsignor_Pedro_de_Foix_Montoya&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Wittkower, Rudolf (1955). <i>Gian Lorenzo Bernini: The Sculptor of the Roman Baroque</i>. London: Phaidon Press. pp.&#160;237\u2013238.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Gian+Lorenzo+Bernini%3A+The+Sculptor+of+the+Roman+Baroque&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pages=237-238&amp;rft.pub=Phaidon+Press&amp;rft.date=1955&amp;rft.aulast=Wittkower&amp;rft.aufirst=Rudolf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABust+of+Monsignor+Pedro+de+Foix+Montoya\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<div role=\"navigation\" class=\"navbox\" aria-labelledby=\"Gian_Lorenzo_Bernini_(works)\" style=\"padding:3px\"><table class=\"nowraplinks vcard collapsible collapsed navbox-inner\" s